cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.DC 

The paper deals with designing utility functions for agents in a multi-agent system to maximize a global utility, specifically in the context of network routing. This falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the mathematics of Collective Intelligence (cs.SI) and uses machine learning algorithms (cs.AI) to improve the performance of the system. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of Braess' paradox, which is related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
